Using the TUN/TAP driver to create a serial network connection
==============================================================

from Thanasis Georgiou

http://thgeorgiou.com/posts/2017-03-20-usb-serial-network/

see too:

 - https://backreference.org/2010/03/26/tuntap-interface-tutorial/

 - http://vtun.info

 - http://linux-ip.net/html/tools-ip-route.html

 - http://jodies.de/ipcalc?host=172.29.250.192&mask1=28&mask2=29

-------------------------------------------------------

To build this cmake project simply use the makefile wrapper::

  make setup
  make check  # use clang-tidy
  make format # use clang-format
  make test
  DESTIDR=/tmp/stagedir make install

  # to create a test-coverage report:
  BUILD_TYPE=Coverage make lcov


extented by Claus Klein
